National integration of science and technologyScience and technology in the United States has a long history, producing many important figures and developments in the field.
[2]Early American science [ edit ]In the early decades of its history, the United States was relatively isolated from Europe and also rather poor.
Technology inflows from abroad have played an important role in the development of the United States, especially in the late nineteenth century.
World War II had a profound impact on the development of science and technology in the United States.
Telecom and technology [ edit ]For the past 80 years, the United States has been integral in fundamental advances in telecommunications and technology.